summary: I honestly feel like Fifteen is not given enough appreciation. Like, this song is so freaking important to young girls...
body:
I honestly feel like Fifteen is not given enough appreciation. Like, this song is so freaking important to young girls especially and girls and women everywhere???? “In your life you’ll do things greater than dating the boy on the football team. I didn’t know if At fifteen.” “Back then I swore I was gonna marry him someday but I realized some bigger dreams of mine. And Abigail gave everything she had to a boy who changed his mind. And we both cried.”

Like, how freaking monumental is this song? I got to grow up from a young age with Taylor contradicting ALL OF FREAKING SOCIETY, that wants to tell girls and women that the person they will marry will be the most important decision they should make and you should make that as young as possible, by telling us that not only does it not matter who we marry, but that we as women and girls are capable of realizing our ‘bigger dreams’ all on our own. And not only that but tells us to be careful about decisions we make when we’re young, because they might not be right for you. “And you just might find who you’re supposed to be. I didn’t know who I was supposed to be at fifteen.”

I just feel like this song is so freaking important okay
